<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-09-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-09-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="1111" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1111">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Adee</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Straus</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-09-20"><hi rend="italic">September 20,
                                    1898</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 5.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of Mr.
                            Riddle’s No. 179, of the 3d instant, transmitting translation of a note
                            verbale from the Sublime Porte on the subject of the regulations
                            prohibiting the entrance of Jews into Turkey.</p>
                        <p>The dispatch has been anticipated by the Department sending the legation
                            copies of the correspondence on the subject with the Turkish minister
                            here.</p>
                        <p>Respectfully, yours,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Alvey A. Adee</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi></signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>